    <h1>Tutorial: Making presentations in LaTeX using Beamer</h1>
    <h2>Step 1: Install LaTeX</h2>
    <p>First, install LaTeX on your system by following the instructions on <a href="https://www.latex-project.org/get/">LaTeX Project website</a>.</p>
    
    <h2>Step 2: Create a LaTeX document</h2>
    <p>Create a new LaTeX document with the following content:</p>
    <pre><code>\documentclass{beamer}
    
\begin{document}

\begin{frame}
    \frametitle{Sample Frame}
    This is a sample frame.
\end{frame}

\end{document}</code></pre>

    <h2>Step 3: Compile the document</h2>
    <p>Compile the LaTeX document using your preferred LaTeX compiler.</p>

